This is one of the nicest properties in the Phoenix area without question.  The entire area is well maintained and truly gives you the sense of being away from the noise and business of everyday life.  Both the guest rooms and common areas are visually pleasing and decorated in a way that blends in with the surroundings.  The food and service are quite good and for a relaxing long weekend, you would be hard pressed to find a better option.  For those with Diamond status, the lounge is definitely one of the better ones and they will go above and beyond to ensure you have a great time.

