80tJzUERJjRDjpxUXy4M6w
Outback has a funny way of making a dish that should be relatively healthy and ruining it.  Don't get me wrong - the flavors are often tasty, but if you are trying to watch what you eat, this is not the place.  My understanding is that they use a garlic-butter sauce for cooking just about everything, which really ruins the healthy aspect of many of the dishes.  If you ask for it to be excluded, it will go a long way towards keeping your meal reasonable.  For a fast casual eatery, Outback is fine.  But if you really want a great steak, there are so many other places to go that won't cost you all that more for much better taste and quality.

