Thunderbird does one thing, and it does it extremely well.  Since 1946, it has served as the pre-eminent international graduate level business school in the US.  Consistently ranked #1 in the world, Thunderbird goes beyond the technical aspects of a business education and attracts those personalities who possess global curiosity.  By focusing on the intangibles, Thunderbird consistently sets itself apart by educating cohorts of students able to adapt and excel in all corners of the globe.  As a veteran, their motto definitely resonates with me: "Borders frequented by trade seldom require soldiers."

